Interface ISeq<K>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Counted, Iterable<K>, Seqable<K>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IChunkedSeq<K>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    APersistentMap.KeySeq, APersistentMap.ValSeq, APersistentVector.RSeq, ArraySeq, ArraySeq.ArraySeq_boolean, ArraySeq.ArraySeq_byte, ArraySeq.ArraySeq_char, ArraySeq.ArraySeq_double, ArraySeq.ArraySeq_float, ArraySeq.ArraySeq_int, ArraySeq.ArraySeq_long, ArraySeq.ArraySeq_short, ASeq, Cons, EnumerationSeq, IterableSeq, PersistentList, PersistentVector.ChunkedSeq, StringSeq

    public interface ISeq<K>
extends Counted, Seqable<K>
    A persistent, functional, sequence interface.

    ISeqs are immutable values, i.e. neither first(), nor rest() changes or invalidates the ISeq.

    This is the equivalent of java.util.Iterator for persistent collections.

    An empty seq is null.
